      </language>
      <purpose>To be used as a part of the assesment level of intubation difficulty before a planned anesthesia.</purpose>
      <keywords>mallampati</keywords>
      <keywords>anaesthetic</keywords>
      <keywords>intubation</keywords>
      <keywords>airway</keywords>
      <use>To be used as a part of the assesment level of intubation difficulty before a planned anesthesia. The examination is done while the patient is sitting, upright with the head in a neutral position, with an open mouth, tongue protuded and without phonation.</use>
      <misuse />
      <copyright>© Nasjonal IKT HF</copyright>
